objects.abstract: Geopolitical analysis (EN) / Pro-Kremlin Disinformation and FIMI Campaigns
objects.content:
Sector: Information Operations

Theme: Pro-Kremlin Disinformation and FIMI Campaigns

Russia continues to leverage AI-enhanced Foreign Information Manipulation and Interference (FIMI) to smear Ukrainian athletes and discredit European institutions (specifically France). Measures also include domestic censorship by banning VPNs and blocking communication platforms like WhatsApp.

Tags: Russia, Disinformation, FIMI, Ukraine, Censorship

objects.abstract: Geopolitical analysis (EN) / AI Ethics and Military Contracts
objects.content:
Sector: Government & Defense

Theme: AI Ethics and Military Contracts

Anthropic has refused a US Department of Defense contract demand to remove guardrails on its Claude AI, citing risks of autonomous weapon misuse and domestic surveillance. This highlights the growing tension between AI vendors and military requirements.

Tags: AI, Anthropic, Pentagon, Ethics, Autonomous Weapons

objects.name: UAT-10027: Deployment of Dohdoor Backdoor
objects.description:
Campaign targeting US education and healthcare sectors since December 2025. It uses phishing and DLL sideloading to install 'Dohdoor', a stealthy backdoor utilizing DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) for C2 through Cloudflare infrastructure.

Analysis:
UAT-10027 utilizes advanced evasion techniques including custom XOR-SUB decryption and NTDLL unhooking. The use of Cloudflare to mask C2 traffic and hijacking legitimate DNS processes via DoH makes this threat particularly difficult to detect with traditional perimeter defenses.

Recommendations:
- Monitor for unusual DoH (DNS-over-HTTPS) traffic and audit PowerShell execution logs.
- Implement strict DLL sideloading protections and application whitelisting.

objects.content: The threat landscape for late February 2026 is dominated by the revelation of long-term zero-day exploitation of Cisco SD-WAN infrastructure by the sophisticated actor UAT-8616. This campaign, active since 2023, underscores a strategic shift toward targeting edge-facing network management systems for persistent access. Simultaneously, large-scale data breaches at ManoMano (38M), Conduent (2.5M), and Odido (2M) highlight systemic supply chain risks through third-party providers. The emergence of 'Dohdoor' malware targeting US critical sectors (Education, Healthcare) with DNS-over-HTTPS techniques further demonstrates the evolution of stealthy C2 mechanisms. Finally, the exposure of Gemini AI API keys signals a new frontier in 'secret leakage' vulnerabilities as AI integration accelerates.
